	"keywords": "React Native, Firebase",
	"description": "Google sign-in is a great login feature to offer to your app&#x27;s users. It makes\nit easier for them to create an account and sign in. \n\nAnd what&#x27;s even better, Firebase makes it extremely easy for developers to add\nsupport for Google sign-in. But setting up the React Native environment can\ncreate some challenges, which are fully covered in this tutorial. \n\nReact Native and Firebase SDK make the implementation of Google login pretty\nstraightforward. Let&#x27;s build a simple app that only has a single G",
